im just alone is this normal im a busy person working going to two schools i was a loner at high school so during my first year of college i joined many clubs and met new people sadly enough i barely clicked with anyone most are superficial and i still felt the high school mentality now im all alone again during my spare time i dont have anyone to talk on the phone im just alone is this normal or am i headed for disaster you know if you are happy being alone there is no problem with that i have found that there are only people in my life that i can spend any amount of time with my husband my best pal from college and my dad you don't need quantitiy of friends but one or two close relationships are good to keep you from becoming too isolated you will meet the quality and type of people you seek by going where you feel best common interests especially if they are very odd ones can be a great start to a friendship what are your hobbies what do you love to do or read or be around spending time working together as a group on something will help you build strong relationships my dad was a woodcarver every wednesday night he met up with a bunch of other people in a school and they sat around and mentored each other on woodcarving techniques talked and really built some good and lasting friendships my husband and i love to travel rescue animals organic farm build things and entertain he has several friends who are car restoration buffs and i hang out with women who like to talk philosophy religion or bake both of us were pretty much loners before we met we brought each other out of our shells but i learned in the process that any common passion for something will build a friendship good luck to you Social rule Friends One Tree Hill (TV series) About a Boy Nicomachean Ethics Carl Jung Undergrads Friendship Kender Asperger syndrome Pitaten Kurt Cobain Sharon Tate The Amber Spyglass Socrates Jiddu Krishnamurti W.I.T.C.H. Infantilism Religious Society of Friends Theory of condu